{
  "text": ", approximately 2-fold larger than in pH 7.4 buffer. This rate constant corresponds to loss of 5% over 24 h, or around 30% leakage over 10 days. The presence of serum in the solution has been shown to increase leakage of calcein from liposomes prepared from either egg PC, DPPC, or DSPC, an effect attributed to membrane destabilization due to serum phospholipid exchange [CITATION_1] . Under acidic conditions doxorubicin becomes progressively protonated, reducing the concentration of the neutral molecule. Therefore, the driving force for leakage increases with decreasing pH [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
